---

Notes on third-party content:

* Climate datasets used as inputs (FORESEE v1.1 by Dobor et al. 2015, World
  Bank CCKP CMIP6 0.25°, HungaroMet open data) retain their own licenses.
  This repository does not redistribute their raw data — only district-level
  aggregates and derived indices.
* The variety knowledge base in `analysis/config/grape_envelopes.csv` is
  curated from published literature (Tonietto & Carbonneau 2004, Hungarian
  Wine Marketing Agency variety profiles, OIV variety descriptors and others).
* The 22 wine-district polygons are dissolved from OpenStreetMap admin level 8
  geometries (© OpenStreetMap contributors, ODbL) using a manually-labelled
  Borvidek attribution.
* The benchmark paper for variety-suitability cross-checks is Lakatos & Nagy
  (2025), Frontiers in Plant Science, doi:10.3389/fpls.2025.1481431
  (CC BY 4.0).
